cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL. 

The paper proposes a method to reduce the parameters of RNNs for computer vision tasks, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. "cs.LG" (Machine Learning) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on developing a new method for training RNNs. "cs.CV" (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also likely as the paper specifically mentions computer vision tasks such as Action Recognition in Videos and Image Captioning. "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) and "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also possible categories as the paper deals with neural networks and their optimization. Finally, "cs.CL" (Computation and Language) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on natural language processing, but it could still be relevant as Image Captioning involves generating natural language descriptions of images.
